Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of traffic sign detection using state-of-the-art and custom convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of neural networks also suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The analysis of the characteristics of the top performing algorithms and the investigation of their robustness suggest that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the reliability assessment of traffic sign detection under inclement conditions, which suggests that it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
